Student Course Registration System
Description
This is a simple command-line application developed using Python and SQLite.
The system helps manage students, courses, and course registrations in a school environment.
This project is created for learning purposes and to practice Python programming and database concepts.
Features
Add students
Add courses
Register students for courses
View student course registrations
Store data using SQLite database
Technologies Used
Python 3
SQLite3
How to Run
Make sure Python 3 is installed
Download or clone the repository
Open a terminal in the project folder
Run the program using: python main.py
Menu Options
Add Student
Add Course
Register Student
View Registrations
Exit
Database Tables
students (student_id, name, department)
courses (course_id, course_name, credit)
registrations (reg_id, student_id, course_id)
Purpose of This Project
Learn Python basics
Practice SQLite database usage
Understand relational database design
Build a simple real-world system
